	#########################################################################################
	### Subwindow_Or_Viewport_Info datatype										# Probably SUBWINDOW_INFO and VIEWPORT_INFO should be in separate types rather than share Subwindow_Or_Viewport_Info.
															# Most of the places we currently use Subwindow_Or_Viewport_Info, only SUBWINDOW_INFO is actually allowed, so we do a
	also														# lot of runtime checking for VIEWPORT_INFO and raising a fatal error if present.  It would be cleaner in
	Subwindow_Or_Viewport_Info											# those cases to have a type including SUBWINDOW_INFO but not VIEWPORT_INFO, eliminating the runtime checks.
	  #														# Obviously we could have a separate Topwindow_Or_Viewport_Info type combining the two for the few cases where both are allowed.
	  = SUBWINDOW_INFO  Subwindow_Info										# 
	  #	
	  | VIEWPORT_INFO     { pixmap:		g2p::Gadget_To_Rw_Pixmap,						# The pixmap visible in the viewport.
				#
				viewports:	Ref( List( Viewport ) ),						# We make this a Ref(List(...)) to allow for adding additional viewports opening onto the same underlying pixmap.
															# WARNING: We don't currently use multiple viewports onto one pixmap; if we start doing so we'll probably find that *VIEWPORT_INFO.is_visible doesn't work right with them.

				is_visible:	Ref( Bool )								# This will be FALSE only if we are one of several alternate views in a TABBED_VIEWS set.
															# We need this so that   update_offscreen_parent_pixmaps_and_then_topwindow()   in   src/lib/x-kit/widget/gui/guiboss-imp.pkg
															# can know when to stop propagating widget updates up the viewport tree.
			      }			



